      "writtenOn": "2017-09-27T21:43:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we need a better one. Default one is mostly targeted for RPCs and stuff like that. It has too many buckets in subsecond range, which makes no sense for scheduler jobs that runs on order of ~10 min or so. What bucketer does CQ use?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "f9c060033e290385d7d9bd73b5c43b2609a9b283",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4550d49e_2c0f8135",
        "filename": "scheduler/appengine/engine/invocation.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 77,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-05T03:08:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "CQ uses mostly 10**0.04 with seconds (up to 2.3 hours). After playing with bucketers, I think I decided to go for 10**0.05037 in seconds, which covers 1s .. 1day.",
      "parentUuid": "553bf35b_dcd5318d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 30
      },
